-- Socar to Start Drilling Israeli Field Next Month, Novosti Says
-- B y   Z u l f u g a r   A g a y e v
-- 2012-09-26T06:10:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-26/socar-to-start-drilling-israeli-field-next-month-novosti-says.html
State Oil Co. of Azerbaijan will
start exploration drilling next month at the Med Ashdod field in
Israel’s part of the Mediterranean Sea, Novosti-Azerbaydzhan
 said , citing Farid Axundov, the head of the state energy
producer’s Caspian Drilling Co. unit  Caspian Drilling plans two exploration wells, Axundov said,
according to the Baku-based news service.  CDC, as the unit is known, agreed with Israel’s  Shemen Oil
& Gas Resources Ltd. (SMOG)  in February 2011 to drill at Med Ashdod,
Novosti-Azerbaydzhan said. The unit was established in 1996 by
the Azeri energy producer, which holds 92.44 percent, and  Santa
Fe  Inc., according to the CDC website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zulfugar Agayev in Baku at 
 zagayev@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
